  "event_preview": "WeatherTech Raceway Laguna Seca is a 2.238-mile (3.602 km) permanent 11-turn road course in Monterey, California, opened in 1957 and defined above all else by the Corkscrew — a blind, left-right drop of nearly 60 feet through Turns 8 and 8A that remains the most recognisable sequence on the North American sports car calendar. The Monterey SportsCar Championship is the fourth round of the 2026 IMSA WeatherTech SportsCar Championship, run over two hours and 40 minutes across GTP, GTD Pro and GTD with a 33-car field. The weekend carries a 1970s throwback theme, with teams encouraged to run retro-inspired liveries.\n\nThe No. 6 Porsche Penske Motorsport Porsche 963 has won the last two Monterey races but is yet to win in 2026. The No. 31 Cadillac Whelen V-Series.R of Earl Bamber and Jack Aitken is the only car in any IMSA class to have podiumed in every race so far this season, with Bamber returning after missing Long Beach for WEC duty. GTD Pro returns to action for the first time since Sebring, with its nine full-season entries including the Pfaff Motorsports Lamborghini Temerario GT3 making its Laguna Seca debut.\n\nThe WeatherTech Championship qualifying record belongs to Sébastien Bourdais, who turned a 1:12.445 (111.212 mph) in the No. 01 Cadillac in May 2024. The GTD Pro record is held by Nicky Catsburg at 1:19.727 (101.054 mph) and in GTD by Kenton Koch at 1:20.810 (99.700 mph), both also from May 2024.",
  "event_preview_ru": "",
